org.elasticsearch.index.percolator

Class PercolatorQueriesRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.elasticsearch.index.shard.AbstractIndexShardComponent
      • org.elasticsearch.index.percolator.PercolatorQueriesRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable, IndexShardComponent

    public final class PercolatorQueriesRegistry
extends AbstractIndexShardComponent
implements java.io.Closeable
    Each shard will have a percolator registry even if there isn't a PercolatorService.TYPE_NAME document type in the index. For shards with indices that have no PercolatorService.TYPE_NAME document type, this will hold no percolate queries.

    Once a document type has been created, the real-time percolator will start to listen to write events and update the this registry with queries in real time.
